cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AR, cs.MS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper presents a toolchain for generating and verifying software programs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of the Prototype Verification System (PVS) specification language. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of contracts to relate the floating-point program to its functional specification. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of round-off error estimation in the verification process. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of finite precision computations and rounding errors.
